my $usage = '[m
ultravnc_repeater.pl:[m
          perl script implementing the ultravnc repeater[m
          proxy pr

otocol.[m
[m
protocol: Listen on one port for vnc clients (default 5900.)[m
          Listen on one port for vnc servers (default 5500.)[m
          Read 250 bytes from connecting vnc client or server.[m
          Accept ID:<string> from clients and servers, connect them[m
          together once both are present.[m
[m
          The string "RFB 000.000\n" is sent to the client (the client[m
          must understand this means send ID:... or host:port.)[m
          Also accept <host>:<port> from clients and make the[m
          connection to the vnc server immediately. [m
[m
          Note there is no authentication or security WRT ID names or[m
          identities; it is up to the client and server to completely[m
          manage that aspect and whether to encrypt the session, etc.[m
[m
usage:  ultravnc_repeater.pl [-r] [client_port [server_port]][m
[m
Use -r to refuse new server/client connections when there is an existing[m

[Kserver/client ID.  The default is to close the previous one.[m
[m
To write to a log file set the env. var ULTRAVNC_REPEATER_LOGFILE.[m
[m
To run in a loop restarting the server if it exits set the env. var.[m
ULTRAVNC_REPEATER_LOOP=1 or ULTRAVNC_REPEATER_LOOP=BG, the latter[m
forks into the background.  Set ULTRAVNC_REPEATER_PIDFILE to a file[m
to store the master pid in.[m
[m
Set ULTRAVNC_REPEATER_NO_RFB=1 to disable sending "RFB 000.000" to[m
the client.  Then this program acts as general TCP rendezvous tool.[m
[m
Examples:[m
[m
        ultravnc_repeater.pl[m
        ultravnc_repeater.pl -r[m
        ultravnc_repeater.pl 5901[m
        ultravnc_repeater.pl 5901 5501[m
[m
        env ULTRAVNC_REPEATER_LOOP=BG ULTRAVNC_REPEATER_LOGFILE=/tmp/u.log ultravnc_repeater.pl ...[m
[m
';[m
[m
use strict;[m
[m
# Set up logging:[m
#[m
if (exists $ENV{ULTRAVNC_REPEATER_LOGFILE}) {[m
        close STDOUT;[m
        if (!open(STDOUT, ">>$ENV{ULTRAVNC_REPEATER_LOGFILE}")) {[m
                die "ultravnc_repeater.pl: $ENV{ULTRAVNC_REPEATER_LOGFILE} $!\n";[m
        }[m
        close STDERR;[m
        open(STDERR, ">&STDOUT");[m
}[m
select(STDERR); $| = 1;[m
select(STDOUT); $| = 1;[m
